The paper deals with wireless communication systems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The focus on machine-type communication (MTC) and noncoherent communication suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of Gabor frames and codebooks suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a protocol for collision resolution, which is a common problem in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
